cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with predicting frames of traffic scenes, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) as the primary domains. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) for enhancing the predicted frames, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the predictions using object detection, which is a sub-domain of graphics (GR).
